narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Latin 110 is a solid introduction and you don't need any background to keep up. It's a very low-key language option. Josh is a good teacher.
Definitely take, it is a very worthwhile class.
If a student is willing to put in the work, I would definitely recommend Latin 110. It has a lot of homework per night, but learning one of the first languages makes up for it.
I would recommend it to a fellow student. It is a language course with the typical daily work load but without the hardest aspects of language learning (speaking, phrases, idioms, etc).
A lot of work but very rewarding. Yes.

Fast paced learning of Latin basics! Take this course if you're learning for a foundational understanding of a very applicable language. The class was also noted to be very good for students of comparative literature.
